title: ERROR: "Received binary image input but resource not configured to accept NHWC layout"
body:
I followed this manual(https://github.com/openvinotoolkit/model_server/blob/develop/docs/ovms_onnx_example.md#option-2-adding-preprocessing-to-the-server-side-building-a-dag-) to experiment and encountered an error

```bash
model_server/example_client# python grpc_binary_client.py --grpc_port 9001 --input_name 0 --output_name 1463 --model_name resnet --batchsize 1
Start processing:
        Model name: resnet
        Images list file: input_images.txt
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "grpc_binary_client.py", line 71, in <module>
    result = stub.Predict(request, 10.0) # result includes a dictionary with all model outputs
  File "/root/anaconda3/envs/openvino_client/lib/python3.7/site-packages/grpc/_channel.py", line 946, in __call__
    return _end_unary_response_blocking(state, call, False, None)
  File "/root/anaconda3/envs/openvino_client/lib/python3.7/site-packages/grpc/_channel.py", line 849, in _end_unary_response_blocking
    raise _InactiveRpcError(state)
grpc._channel._InactiveRpcError: <_InactiveRpcError of RPC that terminated with:
        status = StatusCode.INVALID_ARGUMENT
        details = "Received binary image input but resource not configured to accept NHWC layout"
        debug_error_string = "{"created":"@1631004339.947760100","description":"Error received from peer ipv6:[::1]:9001","file":"src/core/lib/surface/call.cc","file_line":1069,"grpc_message":"Received binary image input but resource not configured to accept NHWC layout","grpc_status":3}"
>
```

what should I do?
